doc.ContractDescription: IGF::CT::IGF THE ICBM FUZE WSIC EFFORT WILL PROVIDE SUPPORT TO THE ICBM FUZE PROGRAM IN ITS EFFORTS TO INTEGRATE, QUALIFY AND CERTIFY THE NEW SANDIA NATIONAL LAB MK21/W87 REPLACEMENT FUZE INTO THE MM III WEAPON SYSTEM.

A NUMBER OF THEORIES HAVE BEEN ADVANCED FOR THE ORIGIN OF LIFE, MANY OF WHICH POSIT RNA OR RNA-LIKE MOLECULES AS BOTH INFORMATION CARRYING AND CATALYTIC ENTITIES, AND ALL OF WHICH ULTIMATELY REQUIRE COMPARTMENTALIZATION OF FUNCTIONAL MOLECULES TO FORM THE EARLIEST CELLS. THIS PROPOSAL INVESTIGATES PHYSICAL MEANS THAT MAY HAVE FACILITATED THE EMERGENCE OF LIFE THROUGH THE LOCALIZATION AND IMPROVEMENT OF RNA CATALYSIS. IT ADDRESSES THE QUESTION HOW DOES LIFE BEGIN AND EVOLVE?, FROM THE 2008 NASA ASTROBIOLOGY ROADMAP. SPECIFICALLY, IT SPEAKS TO GOAL 3, BY SEEKING TO UNDERSTAND GENERAL PHYSICAL AND CHEMICAL PRINCIPLES THAT LED TO THE FIRST CELLS. WE WILL EVALUATE COMPARTMENTALIZATION DRIVEN BY AQUEOUS PHASE SEPARATION AS A POTENTIAL PHYSICOCHEMICAL MECHANISM TO CONCENTRATE AND HELP CHAPERONE THE FOLDING, MULTIPLE TURNOVER, AND EVOLUTION OF RARE CATALYTIC RNA MOLECULES, AND TO FACILITATE THE FORMATION OF PROGENITOR MEMBRANES THAT ENCAPSULATE THESE MOLECULES WITH EXCEPTIONALLY HIGH EFFICIENCY AS A STEP TOWARDS THE FORMATION OF PROTOCELLS. FOUR RESEARCH OBJECTIVES ARE PROPOSED: (1) IDENTIFY AND CHARACTERIZE POTENTIAL NON-MEMBRANOUS COMPARTMENTS (NMCS) FOR CONCENTRATING RNA FROM DILUTE SOLUTION AND DRIVING RNA BASE PAIRING. (2) TEST THESE COMPARTMENTS FOR THEIR ABILITY TO FACILITATE FUNCTION OF KNOWN FUNCTIONAL RNAS. (3) TAKE THOSE COMPARTMENTS FROM OBJECTIVES 1 AND 2 THAT BEST FACILITATE RNA FUNCTION AND TEST FOR THEIR ABILITY TO FACILITATE THE EVOLUTION OF ENHANCED RIBOZYME FUNCTION. (4) ENCAPSULATE THE NMCS INSIDE OF PROGENITOR MEMBRANES. OUR NMCS WILL BE POLYMER-RICH AQUEOUS DROPLETS FORMED BY PHASE SEPARATION. THE PRIMARY FUNCTION TO BE ASSAYED HEREIN IS GAIN OF ENZYMATIC ACTIVITY IN RIBOZYMES, EITHER FROM VERY DILUTE REAGENTS OR BY FACILITATING NATIVE RNA FOLDING (I.E. ACTING AS AN PRIMORDIAL RNA CHAPERONE) AND PRODUCT RELEASE IN MULTIPLE TURNOVER RNA ENZYMES. WE HYPOTHESIZE THAT CLASSES OF RIBOZYMES THAT DID NOT EMERGE IN CONVENTIONAL SELECTION CONDITIONS WILL BE ISOLATED; HIGH-THROUGHPUT SEQUENCING WILL BE USED TO COVER EXCEPTIONAL SEQUENCE SPACE IN SEARCH OF THESE. RNA-CONTAINING NMCS WILL BE STABILIZED AGAINST COALESCENCE BY NANOSCALE AMPHIPHILE ASSEMBLIES ADSORBED AT THE AQUEOUS/AQUEOUS PHASE BOUNDARY. THE RESULTING SEMI-PERMEABLE BOUNDARY WILL NOT BE A BILAYER AND HENCE SHOULD BE AMENABLE TO BOTH FORMATION IN HIGH SALT AND PASSAGE OF LARGE MOLECULES. WE HYPOTHESIZE THAT SUCH A BARRIER COULD SERVE AS A STEP TOWARDS FORMING TRUE BILAYER MEMBRANES THAT ENTRAP AND ENRICH FUNCTIONAL MOLECULES. COLLECTIVELY, THE WORK PROPOSED HERE WILL INVESTIGATE HOW DILUTE, POTENTIALLY CATALYTIC MACROMOLECULES ON PREBIOTIC EARTH COULD HAVE BEEN CONCENTRATED INTO NMCS AND HOW THEIR LOCAL ENVIRONMENT COULD HAVE FACILITATED FOLDING AND CATALYTIC FUNCTION. REGARDING RNA ENZYMES HAVING MULTIPLE TURNOVER, WHICH IS KEY TO LIFE, WE WILL EXPLORE HOW NMCS COULD HAVE CONCENTRATED VERY DILUTE ENZYMES AND SUBSTRATES, AND FACILITATED THE RELEASE OF PRODUCTS FROM THEIR TEMPLATES. THE MAIN SIGNIFICANCE OF OUR FINDINGS FROM AN RNA ENZYME POINT OF VIEW WILL BE TO DEVELOP NOVEL CONCEPTUAL FRAMEWORKS FOR HOW NMCS COULD: (1) CHAPERONE RNA FOLDING, (2) FACILITATE MULTIPLE TURNOVER OF RNA ENZYMES, AND (3) AID IN THE EVOLUTION OF NEW CATALYTIC RNAS.

doc.ContractDescription: THE BEHAVIORAL HEALTH OF THE CREW DURING A MISSION TO MARS MISSION COULD BE CHALLENGED DUE TO THE CONDITIONS REQUIRED BY THE FLIGHT. HOWEVER THERE IS NO STANDARDIZED METHOD TO DETECT AND QUANTIFY THE MAGNITUDE OF THE RISK OR ITS LIKELIHOOD. THE OVERARCHING GOAL OF THIS PROJECT IS TO BUILD ON A SUCCESSFUL RECORD OF UNOBTRUSIVE, SOFTWARE-BASED MEASUREMENT OF BEHAVIORAL HEALTH INDICATORS EG MOOD, COGNITIVE FUNCTION, PHYSICAL AND MENTAL FATIGUE, SLEEP QUALITY TO DEVELOP AN INTEGRATED STANDARDIZED SUITE OF BEHAVIORAL HEALTH MEASUREMENT TOOLS THAT WOULD BE QUITE FEASIBLE TO IMPLEMENT WITHIN THE CONSTRAINTS OF SPACEFLIGHT RESEARCH, GROUND-BASED ANALOGS BOTH SHORT AND LONG DURATION, AND PROLONGED MISSIONS IN ISOLATED, CONFINED, EXTREME ENVIRONMENTS LASTING UP TO 12 MONTHS OR LONGER. ACHIEVEMENT OF THIS GOAL WOULD PERMIT A MORE RAPID AND RELIABLE ASSESSMENT AND QUANTIFICATION OF THE RISK OF ADVERSE BEHAVIORAL CONDITIONS PSYCHIATRIC OUTCOMES FOR EXPLORATION CLASS MISSIONS. THE SUITE OF BEHAVIORAL MEDICINE MEASURES WE ARE DEVELOPING WILL BE INTEGRATED ON APPLE IPAD PLATFORM FOR THEIR STANDARDIZED USE IN GROUND ANALOGS RELEVANT TO THE SPACEFLIGHT CONTEXT IE STANDARDIZED BEHAVIORAL MEASURES TOOL OR SBMT. IT WILL INCLUDE THE COGNITION BATTERY, VISUAL ANALOG SCALES VAS OF PERCEIVED MENTAL AND PHYSICAL EXHAUSTION, FATIGUE, STRESS, WORKLOAD, CONFLICT AND SLEEP QUALITY, ACTIGRAPHY FOR MONITORING SLEEP WAKE ACTIVITY, AN AUDIO JOURNAL, THE SPACE DOCK TASK AS AN OPERATIONAL PERFORMANCE MEASURE, AND ADDITIONAL NON-INVASIVE MEASURES RELEVANT TO BEHAVIORAL MEDICINE INFORMED BY A COMPREHENSIVE LITERATURE REVIEW. THE SBMT WILL BE EVALUATED FOR INCLUSION OF THE TASK OF TAKING THE INFORMATION ON MEASUREMENT FEASIBILITY, FLEXIBILITY AND ACCEPTABILITY DURING POST MISSION ASSESSMENTS IN THE PARTICIPANTS STUDIED IN HERA, HI SEAS AND ON ISS. IT WILL BE IMPROVED AS NEEDED, AND AN OPERATIONAL PROCEDURES DOCUMENT WILL BE DEVELOPED TO MAKE IT USE CONVENIENT AND UNOBTRUSIVE FOR DETECTING THE INCIDENT RATE OF BEHAVIORAL HEALTH RISKS IN SPACE AND ON EARTH.
